6. Contend exceedingly, That 2 Pet. 3. 18. Col. 3. 5, &c.
Grace may still be growing; and sin be dying. The more Grace, and the less Sin: the less like Satan, the more like God;
• he further from Hell, the nearer to Heaven. The Eph. 5. 27. & 4. 12, 13. Abolition of sin, and the Perfection of Grace, are the suburbs of Glory.



And thus I pass from the Dark to the Bright side of
the Text; yet shall ye be as the wings of a Dove covered
with silver, &c. Hence, note;

